SIMPLE: sideling
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sideling
<hw>Side"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sideling</ets>, fr. <ets>side</ets> side. See <er>Side</er>, and
cf. <er>Sidelong</er>, <er>Headlong</er>.]</ety> <def>Sidelong; on the
side; laterally; also, obliquely; askew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fellow nailed up maps . . . some <qex>sideling</qex>, and others
upside down.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sideling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sideling
<hw>Side"ling</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Inclining to one side; directed
toward one side; sloping; inclined; <as>as, <ex>sideling</ex>
ground</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sidelong</ent>⟦br⟧
